# CS224d #1
## Softmax
### RHS to LHS
$$ 
		softmax(\boldsymbol{x}) = \frac{e^{x_i}}{\sum e^{x_i}} = \frac{e^{x_i}}{\sum e^{x_i}} . \frac{e^{c}}{e^{c}} = 
	\frac{e^{x_i + c}}{e^c \sum e^{x_i}} = 
	\frac{e^{x_i + c}}{\sum e^{x_i + c}} = softmax(\boldsymbol{x + c})
$$

### LHS to RHS
It is similar to previous. Just multiply with  $ e^{-c} $

